# Performance baseline. Depends on the top 500 PyPI packages (by
# download count) so each target exercises the full uv hub, whl_install
# fan-out, and venv assembly path. Time `bazel test` of these targets
# (with cold caches: `bazel clean --expunge` first) to track regressions
# in analysis, fetch, build, and runtime startup costs.
#
# Excluded from the dep set because no wheel arm satisfies darwin/arm64
# (the local dev platform):
#   triton                       linux+x86 only
#   pywin32                      windows only
#   pyspark                      sdist-only (depends on host JDK)
#   snowflake-connector-python   ships macosx_x86_64 but no arm64
#   snowflake-sqlalchemy         depends on snowflake-connector-python
# Their transitive cousins (nvidia-*, cuda-*) remain in the lock but are
# only selected by torch's Linux wheel, so they don't fail darwin builds.
load("@aspect_rules_py//py:defs.bzl", "py_library", "py_test")

